  "response": "In January, Orlando experiences cool and mild winter weather. Here are some typical characteristics:\n\nTemperature:\n- Average high temperatures around 72\u00b0F (22\u00b0C)\n- Average low temperatures around 50\u00b0F (10\u00b0C)\n- Relatively cool, but much warmer compared to many other US regions\n\nPrecipitation:\n- Relatively low rainfall\n- Average of about 2.5 inches of rain during the month\n- Less humid compared to summer months\n\nOther conditions:\n- Generally sunny days\n- Occasional cold fronts can bring brief periods of cooler temperatures\n- Very rare chance of freezing temperatures\n- Typically comfortable for outdoor activities\n- Good weather for theme parks and tourist attractions\n\nClothing recommendations:\n- Light jacket or sweater for mornings and evenings\n- Layers are recommended\n- Comfortable long pants\n- Occasional need for a warmer coat during cold fronts\n\nOverall, January in Orlando offers mild, pleasant winter weather that is much more comfortable compared to many other parts of the United States.",
